1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:06,416
This programme contains scenes which
some viewers may find upsetting.

2
00:00:06,440 --> 00:00:09,456
A peace treaty has been ratified
with the Emperor of France.

3
00:00:09,480 --> 00:00:10,656
It'll come to war again.

4
00:00:10,680 --> 00:00:13,096
I am in love with Sonya and
I want us to be married.

5
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:14,416
You had better know that

6
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:17,056
I can never recognise that
intriguer as my daughter!

7
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:19,056
My father made it a
condition of his consent

8
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:20,936
that the marriage not
take place for a year.

9
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:22,736
I'll wait.

10
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:25,096
- You're so lovely.
- You mustn't say that!

11
00:00:25,120 --> 00:00:26,560
Why ever not?

12
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:30,176
Will you tell Prince Andrei when he comes

13
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:32,016
that our engagement is at an end -

14
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:33,776
and I cannot be his wife.

15
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,896
He loves me, Sonya!

16
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:38,456
I'd do anything - I'd run away with him!

17
00:00:38,480 --> 00:00:40,456
You're to come with us, sir.

18
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:42,216
We've been betrayed!

19
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:43,696
No!

20
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:45,736
I will go to him, wherever he is!

21
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:48,160
He's a married man, he
has a wife in Poland!

22
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:51,360
[SHE SOBS]

23
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,440
[DOOR OPENS]

24
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:58,216
Andrei, I'm so sorry about this.

25
00:01:58,240 --> 00:02:00,456
Yes, well...

26
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:04,256
Just to confirm, I have received
a refusal from Countess Rostova,

27
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:05,536
and rumours have reached me

28
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:08,176
about an intrigue with your brother-in-law.
Is that correct?

29
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,496
Yes, but that's all over.
Anatole has left Moscow.

30
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:12,656
Well, it makes no difference.

31
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,096
When you see Countess Rostova,

32
00:02:14,120 --> 00:02:16,296
tell her that she was
and is completely free,

33
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,736
and I wish her no ill.

34
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:19,160
Is that all?

35
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:22,896
Look here, I'm sure it
was a moment of madness,

36
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:25,376
and she regrets it bitterly.

37
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:28,936
She loves you, I'm sure
of it, and you love her.

38
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,456
Remember when you came to me

39
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:33,200
and told me how madly you
were in love with her?

40
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:40,296
I know you believe a fallen woman
should be forgiven, Pierre,

41
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:42,456
and I admire you for it.

42
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:44,936
But I'm a different sort of man.

43
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:47,280
I cannot forgive, and I WILL not.

44
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,976
Here are her letters, and her portrait.

45
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,496
I would be grateful if you
would return them to her.

46
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:57,000
Andrei, think how she must be suffering.

47
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,120
Will you do as I ask?

48
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:05,616
Yes, of course.

49
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:07,040
Then take them.

50
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,616
And if we are to remain friends,

51
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:12,240
I ask you never to speak
to me about this again.

52
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,040
Goodbye.

53
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,360
[DOOR CLOSES]

54
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,760
[DOOR OPENS]

55
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:54,176
You're not well.

56
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,696
I wish I were dead.

57
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:59,760
No... No, no, don't say that.

58
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:06,960
What did he say?

59
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:11,816
Only that you are free,
have always been free,

60
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,600
and he bears you no ill will.

61
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:16,200
Yes, that's like him.

62
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:21,016
I know it's all over.

63
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:24,440
And I'm tormented by the
wrong I've done him.

64
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:28,320
But will you...?

65
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:32,440
[SHE WEEPS]

66
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:36,680
Will you ask him if he can forgive me?

67
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,496
Of course I will.

68
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,800
But, Natasha...

69
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:44,896
What happened? How did it come about?

70
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:49,056
Did you...? Did you love that scoundrel?

71
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,296
Don't call him that!

72
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:52,816
I don't know.

73
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:55,016
I don't know anything any more.

74
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,440
I'm so unhappy.

75
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:00,720
I've spoilt everything, haven't I?

76
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:05,136
Don't try to talk about it now.

77
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:10,576
Later, when your soul is clear,
remember, I'm always your friend.

78
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:17,496
If you need help, or advice, or just to pour
your soul out, remember me, dear Natasha.

79
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:19,520
Don't talk to me like that.

80
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:22,080
I don't deserve it.

81
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:25,176
I'm ruined, aren't I?

82
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:28,176
No - for God's sake, no. Listen.

83
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:30,896
If I were not married myself,
and a better man than I am -

84
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:33,016
I mean, worthy of you -

85
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:35,616
I would go down on my knees this minute

86
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:38,160
and ask for your hand and your love.

87
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:42,880
Oh...

88
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,320
Pierre...

89
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,960
Courage, mademoiselle.

90
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:31,256
Oh, Ilya, when shall we
have our Natasha back?

91
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:34,256
The doctor says she's making
good progress, physically.

92
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:36,696
It's as if the spirit were gone from her.

93
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:39,616
She doesn't want to read,
or talk, or sing...

94
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:42,256
Pierre seems to bring her a little comfort.

95
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:46,696
We should never have let her engage
herself to that cold-hearted man!

96
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:49,816
To gain her affections and then
leave her alone for a year -

97
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:52,360
almost as if he wanted her to betray him!

98
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:58,120
Oh, Ilya...

99
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:01,240
where's our lovely girl gone?

100
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:24,176
Oh, God, in your mercy, forgive me,

101
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:26,760
and show me the way to lead a better life.

102
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:31,040
[CHEERING]

103
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:36,000
- <font color="#000000">CHANTING</font>:
- Vive I'Empereur! Vive I'Empereur!

104
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:47,080
Across the river, Russia.

105
00:07:49,400 --> 00:07:51,280
The time has come, gentlemen.

106
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:53,760
Sound the advance.

107
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:03,976
This breach of our treaty
cannot and will not be endured.

108
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,416
<fONT COLOR="#000000">ALL</FONT>: - Hear, hear!

109
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:07,216
I will not make peace with that man

110
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:10,960
unless he withdraws every one of
his soldiers from Russian soil!

111
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:14,920
Drubetskoy.

112
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:17,960
Come here.

113
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:25,360
I appoint you to take
my message to Napoleon.

114
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:30,200
I thank Your Majesty for this great honour.

115
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:36,616
Make sure he understands.

116
00:08:36,640 --> 00:08:40,296
Not one single French soldier
to remain on Russian soil.

117
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:42,760
Now, go - and may God be with you.

118
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,760
Wait here, sir.

119
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,736
Monsieur Drubetskoy.

120
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:26,720
- Sire, the Emperor...
- You are very young.

121
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:33,736
I do not want war and
I never wanted it.

122
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:37,376
Your master has brought
it all upon himself.

123
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:40,496
He could have had Moldavia and Wallachia.

124
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:42,320
Let him bear the consequences.

125
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:46,136
Your generals have no stomach for a fight.

126
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:49,616
- On... On the contrary, Your Majesty...
- Don't argue with me.

127
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:51,896
I know everything.

128
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:55,056
I know the state of your miserable army.

129
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:57,856
You have 200,000 men. I
have three times that.

130
00:09:57,880 --> 00:10:00,216
Sire, if you are prepared
to withdraw your troops

131
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:03,280
beyond the Neman, then the
Emperor will negotiate.

132
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:08,056
C'est trop tard, mon petit.

133
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,496
It's too late.

134
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:11,416
I'm going to take your country.

135
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:13,456
But it's all right.

136
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:15,080
It's not your fault.

137
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:19,440
Tell your master he'll receive my letter.

138
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:27,416
It's considered a great honour, monsieur,

139
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:30,120
to have one's ear pulled by the Emperor.

140
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:34,000
Oh, right... Thank you.

141
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:45,336
Well, we're at war again.

142
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:48,976
Napoleon's crossed the Neman and
he's advancing towards Smolensk.

143
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,456
- Oh, Ilya!
- Don't fret, my dear,

144
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:54,416
he'll be driven back before
he gets anywhere near Moscow.

145
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:56,136
But Nikolai...

146
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:58,256
Nikolai's a seasoned officer now.

147
00:10:58,280 --> 00:11:00,336
He knows how to look after himself.

148
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:02,976
All we can do is hope and pray.

149
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,656
- Papa, let me enlist!
- Absolutely not!

150
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:07,856
I won't allow it - a boy of 15!

151
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:10,896
All my friends are volunteering!

152
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:14,760
If you won't find me a commission,
I'll run away and find one myself!

153
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:23,306
- It might be best to let him join up...
- Ilya!

154
00:11:23,330 --> 00:11:25,880
Find him a billet where
he can look the part, but...

155
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:28,560
stay out of danger.

156
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:31,280
Is anywhere safe now?

157
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:43,736
Ah, Tikhon - it's good to see you.

158
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:46,736
- How are things?
- All well, Your Excellency.

159
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:49,656
Ah, we have been waiting and
waiting for your arrival!

160
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:52,136
Do step in, Prince Andrei!

161
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:53,656
Do I need your invitation?

162
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:55,976
- No, of course...
- Are you mistress of this house now?

163
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,656
No, not at all...

164
00:11:57,680 --> 00:12:00,376
Where are my father and Princess Marya?
And my son?

165
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,440
Inside, waiting for you, Prince.

166
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:07,120
Papa! Papa!

167
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:13,136
How are you, Masha?

168
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:15,736
So, you're going to war again?

169
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:17,936
Run along.

170
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:20,536
What else is there for me to do?

171
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:22,376
The French grow closer by the day.

172
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:24,040
I wish you could stay with us.

173
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:28,136
Your little boy hardly knows you.

174
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,840
Well, it can't be helped.

175
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:38,496
I hope you're finding my son a
responsive pupil, Monsieur Dessales?

176
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:40,656
Oh, yes. Of course, he's still very young,

177
00:12:40,680 --> 00:12:43,336
but already I detect a certain
gift for la mathematique.

178
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:46,280
Ah! Unlike his Aunt Marya, here!

179
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,416
The hours I've wasted,

180
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:52,056
trying to instil the principles
of algebra and geometry

181
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:53,896
into that muddled little head!

182
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:58,176
Ah, we ladies, the higher studies
are not for us, I think!

183
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:00,656
We have a different kind
of wisdom, you know?

184
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:03,576
[HE CHUCKLES]
- And what might that be?

185
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:06,656
If you don't know, Prince, far
be it for me to tell you!

186
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:09,280
[LAUGHTER]

187
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:14,736
I see you were entertaining your
idiotic pilgrims again today, Marya.

188
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:16,856
They're good people, Father.

189
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:21,056
They know when they're onto a good
thing, I'll say that for them!

190
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:23,040
How can anyone be so gullible?

191
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,656
I know, I know. I see you looking at me.

192
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:32,576
I should treat her more kindly.

193
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:37,336
But she drives me to distraction
with her stupid religiosity -

194
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:41,576
the way she moons about the house
with her eyes full of tears.

195
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:44,376
What's she got to be mournful about?

196
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:48,256
La Bourienne - now, she
makes the most of herself.

197
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:50,360
She makes herself agreeable! Eh?

198
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:53,736
If you're asking me...

199
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:55,760
I wouldn't have said it, but as you ask...

200
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:59,416
I think you treat Marya abominably,

201
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:02,776
when anyone can see how much she
loves you and respects you.

202
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,736
And, again, if you ask me,

203
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:07,656
I think that French woman
stirs things up between you.

204
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,816
She should never have been
my sister's companion.

205
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:11,240
She's not worthy.

206
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:15,936
So, that's it! You had
to say it, didn't you?

207
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:18,736
I didn't want to judge, but you did ask.

208
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:20,960
And, Father, you know that I'm right.

209
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:23,880
How DARE you?

210
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:28,096
GET OUT!

211
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:30,680
I don't want to see your face any more!

212
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:50,696
Once upon a time, there
was a very great nobleman

213
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:52,880
and his name was Bluebeard.

214
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:58,616
Now, this nobleman had a
beautiful young wife,

215
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,576
but she died,

216
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:04,336
and some people thought that
it was Bluebeard's fault,

217
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:06,240
but didn't dare say so.

218
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:11,816
And then, one day, Bluebeard
thought to himself,

219
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:15,600
"It's about time I got myself
another beautiful, young wife..."

220
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:23,960
Tell the story, Papa, tell it!

221
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:27,776
Papa!

222
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:29,816
- Come here, I'll tell you the story.
[DOOR OPENS]

223
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,696
But I want Papa to tell it!

224
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,216
[DOOR SHUTS]

225
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:35,336
Just come and say goodbye to him.

226
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:37,056
I will not! Go away!

227
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:40,176
But Andrei's leaving... Think!
You may never see him again!

228
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:43,136
And whose fault is that? You
made me quarrel with him!

229
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:44,720
I blame YOU for this!

230
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:49,920
[DOOR SLAMS and SHE SHIVERS]

231
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:22,816
Andrei, I wish you didn't have to go.

232
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,120
Thank God I can.

233
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:28,360
- It's a shame that you can't.
- Why do you say that?

234
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:31,776
When you're going to that dreadful war

235
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:33,800
and Papa's so old that he may not...

236
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:37,416
Andrei, let me ask you one thing -

237
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:39,920
don't go with bitterness in your heart.

238
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:44,656
Only forgiveness will make us truly happy.

239
00:16:44,680 --> 00:16:48,336
Forgiveness is a woman's virtue.
I'm not capable of it.

240
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:52,856
When I see Anatole Kuragin again, I
shall challenge him and kill him.

241
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:55,320
And then, perhaps, my
mind will be at peace.

242
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:08,560
[CARRIAGE RUMBLES]
[HOOFBEATS, RUMBLING]

243
00:17:16,080 --> 00:17:20,120
[PIANO PLAYS SOFTLY]
[GENTLE HUMMING]

244
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:29,936
I wish you would play again
properly, and sing again.

245
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:33,256
Sometimes I try, but it
feels wrong, you know?

246
00:17:33,280 --> 00:17:36,296
As if I've no voice left to sing with.

247
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:38,176
It will come again.

248
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,320
You've been very ill. You
know, it takes time.

249
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:44,536
- What I did to Andrei...
- He should have forgiven you.

250
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:46,936
To leave you alone for a
year for no good reason -

251
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:49,936
and how could you have known
what sort of man Kuragin is?

252
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:52,016
Natasha, you made one mistake,

253
00:17:52,040 --> 00:17:54,376
in a life that's all
been bringing happiness

254
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,400
to everyone you know - one mistake!

255
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:59,616
I mean, look at me.

256
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:02,256
My life is one mistake after another.

257
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:03,696
Is that how you see it?

258
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:05,496
How could I see it otherwise?

259
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:09,256
I wanted to change the world for
the better, help my fellow men

260
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:12,656
and look at me - a fat, drunken aristocrat

261
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:14,936
who makes a bungle out of everything.

262
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:17,696
Natasha, I've done nothing
with my life, nothing!

263
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:19,536
You've been very kind to me.

264
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:23,480
And that's only because I...
Never mind.

265
00:18:25,240 --> 00:18:27,040
No-one's as kind as you.

266
00:18:28,960 --> 00:18:31,840
No-one understands me as well as you do.

267
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,216
If you hadn't have been
there - then, and now -

268
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:37,656
I don't know what would have
happened to me, because...

269
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:40,696
If you knew how...
No, this is wrong!

270
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,200
What? What's wrong?

271
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:49,160
Natasha, I think...

272
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:53,480
I think it's best if I
don't visit you so often.

273
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:56,400
But why?

274
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:00,360
Because I...

275
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:03,840
Tell me.

276
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:20,040
[RETREATING FOOTSTEPS]

277
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:34,296
First, get some stationery - eight quires.

278
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:38,176
Here's a sample, exactly the same,
get it from Minsky's, nowhere else -

279
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:41,976
and varnish, sealing wax...
It's all on this list.

280
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:44,256
Give my compliments to the
Governor of Smolensk...

281
00:19:44,280 --> 00:19:47,216
But, Papa, the French are
already approaching Smolensk!

282
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:49,936
They're on our doorstep. Didn't
you read Andrei's letter?

283
00:19:49,960 --> 00:19:53,320
Nonsense, don't interfere! Off
you go, Tikhon! Off you go.

284
00:19:58,560 --> 00:19:59,976
Tikhon.

285
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,616
Go to the Governor, tell him
my father refuses to leave,

286
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:04,696
and ask him what can be done for us.

287
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:07,176
For how many days will
we still be safe here?

288
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:09,776
All right, Princess. I'll
see how the land lies.

289
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,656
And come back quickly.

290
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:12,920
Safe journey!

291
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:17,760
No, no, no, she can't...

292
00:20:18,760 --> 00:20:21,600
The French can't be near Smolensk already.

293
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:24,720
No, no, no, no...

294
00:20:57,880 --> 00:21:01,400
[BUSTLE NEARBY]

295
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:07,120
[CLATTERING AND CHATTER]

296
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:19,696
The town is surrendered!

297
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:20,840
Leave! Leave!

298
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:24,240
Turn it round!

299
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:29,240
[HE PANTS]

300
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:46,360
[SHOUTING, BUSTLE]

301
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,896
Done for! Russia's done for!

302
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:11,056
Go ahead, boys, take the lot!

303
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:13,256
Leave nothing for the French!

304
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:15,080
I'll set the fire myself.

305
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:26,456
Tikhon! What in God's
name are you doing here?

306
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:28,376
The master refused to leave, sir.

307
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,856
Tell him he must!

308
00:22:29,880 --> 00:22:32,216
Tell him the French will be
at Bald Hills within days!

309
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:35,456
Do you understand? He MUST
leave now, as must you!

310
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:37,096
Yes, Your Excellency.

311
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:38,456
Is everything lost now, then?

312
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:40,656
Far from it. But, for now, you have to go!

313
00:22:40,680 --> 00:22:42,000
GO!

314
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:47,360
[FIRE ROARS]

315
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:56,416
- No! No!
- But, Papa, Andrei said...!

316
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:59,576
Did he think I would abandon my
home to that accursed Frenchman?

317
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:00,776
Never!

318
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,976
Bald Hills must be
defended, to the last man!

319
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,960
Summon the militia! Give me my jacket.

320
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:08,656
Not that one! The full dress uniform!

321
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:11,936
Papa, the militia aren't here any more!
Everyone's going!

322
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:15,016
They would never dare disobey me!
You go, if you want to.

323
00:23:15,040 --> 00:23:16,816
I'm making my stand here!

324
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:18,616
Tikhon, buckle my sword!

325
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:21,560
Do it!

326
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:42,400
Grandpa's going to war, isn't he?

327
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:53,120
[SHE GASPS]
Quickly!

328
00:23:55,280 --> 00:23:56,760
Papa!

329
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:01,080
[HE MURMURS IN COHERENTLY]

330
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:07,856
[HE MOANS]
We must carry him to Bogucharovo!

331
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:10,720
We'll be safe there for a while, at least.

332
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,576
Carry on. I'm going to take a detour.

333
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:23,336
There's a place ahead where the
men can bathe, if they want to.

334
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:24,720
Very good, Your Excellency.

335
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:37,120
[QUIET BIRDSONG]

336
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:41,760
[GIRLS GIGGLE]

337
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:46,280
[GIGGLING]

338
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:53,080
[THEY LAUGH]

339
00:25:03,520 --> 00:25:05,400
[THEY GIGGLE]

340
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:43,776
Good day, Master.

341
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:45,176
Where are the family?

342
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,640
All gone away, sir.

343
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:51,240
THANK GOD FOR THAT.

344
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:11,576
It's all right, Your
Excellency, it's not too cold.

345
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:13,816
If you fancy it, I could
order this lot out,

346
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:16,736
- you could have it to yourself.
- No, no, let them bathe.

347
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:21,120
[THEY LAUGH AND TALK]
So much healthy flesh.

348
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:24,936
<font color="#000000">(AND ALL OF IT CANNON FODDER.)</font>

349
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:26,720
[MEN CHATTER]

350
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:43,160
[HE GROANS]

351
00:26:46,080 --> 00:26:48,816
May I be of any assistance,
Your Excellency?

352
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:51,536
No, thank you. We're going to
our estate in Bogucharovo.

353
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:53,816
- It's over there.
- I wouldn't advise it.

354
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:55,976
The French are only two days behind us.

355
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:58,200
Go to Moscow. You'll be safe there.

356
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,160
[PRINCE NIKOLAI GROANS]

357
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:42,040
Dear heart...

358
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:46,840
Daughter...

359
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:51,120
My heart aches...

360
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:56,536
Forgive me.

361
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:58,360
Of course I forgive you, Papa.

362
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:04,760
Andryushka...

363
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:08,560
I want to see him.

364
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:14,496
[TEARFULLY]
- He can't come, Papa.

365
00:28:14,520 --> 00:28:16,416
He's away, with the Army.

366
00:28:16,440 --> 00:28:17,760
[HE MOANS]

367
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:21,320
Russia lost...

368
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:25,600
They destroyed her.

369
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:31,240
Pu...

370
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:34,200
Pu...

371
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:37,360
What is it, dear?

372
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:41,240
Put on your white dress.

373
00:28:43,320 --> 00:28:44,840
I like it.

374
00:29:30,600 --> 00:29:32,000
Tikhon...

375
00:29:36,160 --> 00:29:38,680
Tikhon, I wished for his death...!

376
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:43,480
I prayed for it, and all
the while, he loved me!

377
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:49,520
[HE SNIFFLES]
He loved me...

378
00:30:28,520 --> 00:30:31,736
As soon as we've buried my father,
we must all leave for Moscow.

379
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:34,056
Are you sure this is the best?
If we stayed,

380
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:37,496
I am sure we would be very
well-treated by the French officers.

381
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:40,256
I won't stay to see the
enemy in my father's house.

382
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:42,656
- If you please, Your Excellency?
- Yes, what?

383
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:45,056
The peasants are making
difficulties about the horses.

384
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:48,736
You see? They know they, too, will
be well-treated by my countrymen.

385
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:51,616
The French will put us
under their protection.

386
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:53,483
Truly, Princess, it
will be for the best...

387
00:30:53,507 --> 00:30:56,176
I would rather die
than beg my enemy to protect me.

388
00:30:56,200 --> 00:30:58,576
It would be an insult
to my father's memory.

389
00:30:58,600 --> 00:31:00,856
Tikhon, I am sure this must
be a misunderstanding -

390
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:03,256
send Dron the Head Man to me, please.
Immediately.

391
00:31:03,280 --> 00:31:05,440
They're waiting outside, Your Excellency.

392
00:31:23,320 --> 00:31:25,576
Dronushka, what is this?

393
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:28,216
Now, after our misfortune?

394
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:30,056
We all walk under God, Princess.

395
00:31:30,080 --> 00:31:33,656
I need to leave, this evening, or
tomorrow morning at the latest.

396
00:31:33,680 --> 00:31:36,736
Can you have the horses
ready and the carts loaded?

397
00:31:36,760 --> 00:31:38,856
There are no horses, Princess.

398
00:31:38,880 --> 00:31:41,696
Of course there are horses!
What are you talking about?

399
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:43,616
It's God's punishment, Princess.

400
00:31:43,640 --> 00:31:46,256
Most of the horses were taken for the Army,

401
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:48,136
and, as for the rest of them,

402
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:50,296
there's nothing left to feed them with.

403
00:31:50,320 --> 00:31:52,096
Lies!

404
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:54,856
What it is, Your Excellency,
they've got it into their heads

405
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:57,256
that they'd be better off
waiting for the French.

406
00:31:57,280 --> 00:31:58,816
You haven't understood.

407
00:31:58,840 --> 00:32:01,416
You have my word that you
will be housed and fed

408
00:32:01,440 --> 00:32:03,096
at our estate near Moscow.

409
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:05,656
If you stay, the enemy will destroy you.

410
00:32:05,680 --> 00:32:08,056
The French will set us
free and give us land!

411
00:32:08,080 --> 00:32:09,736
What have you ever done for us?

412
00:32:09,760 --> 00:32:11,976
How can you say that?!

413
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:15,536
You wouldn't dare to if my father
were alive or my brother were here.

414
00:32:15,560 --> 00:32:18,400
Now, I order you to have the
horses ready for departure!

415
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:36,016
Beautiful country - we should
find plenty of fodder here.

416
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:38,816
We need to secure it before
the French get to it.

417
00:32:38,840 --> 00:32:41,096
And a few pretty girls?

418
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:43,456
Mine's the little one in front.

419
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:46,456
- Whoa, whoa, whoa...
- What can we do for you, sweet-face?

420
00:32:46,480 --> 00:32:49,016
My mistress wishes to know
your name and your regiment,

421
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:51,816
if you please, and if you would
come to the house and speak to her.

422
00:32:51,840 --> 00:32:55,256
Certainly. I'm Lieutenant Ilyin
of the Pavlograd Hussars

423
00:32:55,280 --> 00:32:57,576
and this is Count Rostov,
our squadron commander.

424
00:32:57,600 --> 00:32:59,856
And we will be delighted to
speak with your mistress -

425
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:01,256
might we know her name?

426
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:05,296
She is the Princess Marya Nikolayevna
Bolkonskaya, Your Excellency.

427
00:33:05,320 --> 00:33:07,816
Her father, the Prince, died yesterday,

428
00:33:07,840 --> 00:33:11,016
and the peasants have been taking
advantage of the situation.

429
00:33:11,040 --> 00:33:13,600
I am sorry to hear of it.
Please show us the way.

430
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:17,960
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

431
00:33:24,680 --> 00:33:27,296
I am ashamed to have to beg
for your assistance, sir.

432
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:29,896
Not at all, Princess. This is an outrage,

433
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:33,016
and I am only too happy
to be able to assist you.

434
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:35,936
It will be both a pleasure and an
honour to escort you away from here

435
00:33:35,960 --> 00:33:39,040
and I promise you, no-one will
dare cause you any trouble.

436
00:33:45,680 --> 00:33:47,760
Thank you, Count Rostov.

437
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:23,896
My dear Prince, can it be true?

438
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:25,496
Smolensk in flames,

439
00:34:25,520 --> 00:34:28,296
and Napoleon advancing on Moscow?

440
00:34:28,320 --> 00:34:31,376
Oh, our army will stop
him well before Moscow,

441
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:35,256
and you know, Moscow is a
long way from Petersburg.

442
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:39,296
But if it comes to the worst,
what is to happen to us?

443
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:41,336
Are we all to be guillotined?

444
00:34:41,360 --> 00:34:44,136
No, no, no, dear lady,
Napoleon is magnanimous.

445
00:34:44,160 --> 00:34:48,000
I suppose, we shall all have to
brush up our French again, though.

446
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:52,696
Ah, Bilibin! Interesting times we live in.

447
00:34:52,720 --> 00:34:54,936
The lovely Helene not here this evening?

448
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:58,320
Ah, no - she had to accept
another invitation.

449
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:09,296
Two lovers, one absent husband,

450
00:35:09,320 --> 00:35:12,120
and she's in a delicate condition.

451
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:16,840
Of course, the child is not Bezukhov's.

452
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:20,280
I'm sure she'll sort it out.

453
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:26,160
Marry me...

454
00:35:27,560 --> 00:35:30,256
and I'd be yours and yours alone.

455
00:35:30,280 --> 00:35:33,576
That's impossible... isn't it?

456
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:36,216
- Aren't you still married to Bezukhov?
- No!

457
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:38,120
Well, only in name.

458
00:35:39,240 --> 00:35:40,680
You see, we've...

459
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:43,160
He's never...

460
00:35:45,040 --> 00:35:47,096
I can't say it in modesty...

461
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:48,520
You're saying...

462
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:51,776
it could be annulled?

463
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:53,856
Why not?

464
00:35:53,880 --> 00:35:57,016
I'm sure if I write to Pierre,
he'll do anything I asked.

465
00:35:57,040 --> 00:35:59,000
He's such an obliging soul.

466
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:05,936
You do want to marry me, don't you?

467
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:09,440
Well... Yes, of course!

468
00:36:13,120 --> 00:36:15,000
Then I'll write to Pierre directly.

469
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:28,696
You're still wasting your time,

470
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:30,976
turning over cards like a little boy?

471
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:33,776
I'm trying to determine my fate, Catiche.

472
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:36,296
Someone told me that you
were going to the war.

473
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:38,376
Yes, I'm considering it.

474
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:40,016
You?

475
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:42,080
You know nothing about war.

476
00:36:46,200 --> 00:36:48,440
Then perhaps it's time I found out.

477
00:36:54,440 --> 00:36:56,456
[ROSTOV]
My dear mother and father,

478
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:59,216
'I hope you are making
plans to leave Moscow.

479
00:36:59,240 --> 00:37:02,136
'Otradnoye will be much safer for you.

480
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:06,256
'As for myself, you will be happy
to hear that I am well and safe.

481
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:09,056
'The Pavlograd Hussars
have been held in reserve,

482
00:37:09,080 --> 00:37:12,376
'so I have been buying new
horses for the regiment.

483
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:15,016
'We're in a beautiful part of the country.

484
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:18,656
'No-one would think that we were at war.'

485
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:21,136
"A short time ago, I was
able to be of service

486
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:25,136
- "to Princess Marya Bolkonskaya..."
- Ah!

487
00:37:25,160 --> 00:37:27,776
"The family estate was in the
path of the French advance,"

488
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:29,856
"and as I happened to be in the area,"

489
00:37:29,880 --> 00:37:32,696
"I was happy to escort the
Princess for part of her journey"

490
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:34,856
"to a place of greater safety."

491
00:37:34,880 --> 00:37:38,056
"She was very grateful,
as you can imagine..."

492
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:40,696
There's a bit crossed out
there, can't read it.

493
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:45,696
"And asked me to send her
warmest good wishes to you all."

494
00:37:45,720 --> 00:37:46,896
Well!

495
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:48,736
If something should come of that,

496
00:37:48,760 --> 00:37:50,536
it could solve all our problems.

497
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:53,696
'I will soon be arriving in
Voronezh, where I have been invited

498
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:56,336
'to spend the evening with
the Governor and his wife.

499
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:58,696
'I understand they're old friends of yours,

500
00:37:58,720 --> 00:38:01,680
'so I am very much looking
forward to meeting them.'

501
00:38:03,680 --> 00:38:06,616
Ah, here they are, the men of the moment!

502
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:09,496
You are welcome, gentlemen!
Please - take a drink.

503
00:38:09,520 --> 00:38:10,696
Thank you.

504
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:12,600
[LAUGHTER AND CHATTER]

505
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:18,840
- Rich pickings.
[ROSTOV CHUCKLES]

506
00:38:21,160 --> 00:38:23,936
It is such a pleasure to meet you at last.

507
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:25,696
A pleasure for me, too.

508
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:28,736
We heard of your rescue of Princess Marya.

509
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:31,696
Ah! Well, it was fortunate
that I was passing.

510
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:34,456
You made a great impression
upon the Princess.

511
00:38:34,480 --> 00:38:37,455
Did you know that she's here
in Voronezh, with her aunt?

512
00:38:37,479 --> 00:38:40,416
- Really?
- Yes, she is.

513
00:38:40,440 --> 00:38:43,176
And, of course, you will call
upon her tomorrow morning,

514
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:45,016
to pay your respects.

515
00:38:45,040 --> 00:38:47,216
I should be very pleased to see her again.

516
00:38:47,240 --> 00:38:49,176
You know, it's just the match for you.

517
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:51,616
Would you like me to arrange it?

518
00:38:51,640 --> 00:38:53,120
If only it were that simple.

519
00:38:58,040 --> 00:39:01,628
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]
[DOOR OPENS]

520
00:39:01,653 --> 00:39:02,848
He's here!

521
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:15,920
[THEY GIGGLE]

522
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:20,640
Count Rostov.

523
00:39:22,600 --> 00:39:24,216
Princess.

524
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:27,296
I was so happy to hear
you were in Voronezh.

525
00:39:27,320 --> 00:39:30,011
It really does seem
like fate, doesn't it?

526
00:39:30,035 --> 00:39:31,035
Yes, it does.

527
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:33,896
I hope your family are well.

528
00:39:33,920 --> 00:39:36,856
Yes, very well - that is to
say, my sister was quite ill,

529
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:38,656
but I believe she's recovering now.

530
00:39:38,680 --> 00:39:40,056
Oh, I hope so.

531
00:39:40,080 --> 00:39:42,256
I liked her very much when I met her,

532
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:44,016
and I hope to see more of her.

533
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:45,440
I hope you do.

534
00:39:48,040 --> 00:39:51,120
Strange how things turn
out sometimes, isn't it?

535
00:39:52,880 --> 00:39:54,320
Yes, it is.

536
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:12,840
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

537
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:27,880
Ah, Prince Andrei!

538
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:30,560
Welcome back, Your Grace.

539
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:34,805
I'm delighted to be
under your command again.

540
00:40:34,829 --> 00:40:38,536
- Good lad!
- I'm very glad to see you.

541
00:40:38,560 --> 00:40:39,960
How is your father?

542
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:43,776
I learned of his death only yesterday.

543
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:46,856
Oh! I'm so, so sorry to hear that.

544
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:48,720
I loved and respected him.

545
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:52,280
He was a great soldier in his day.

546
00:40:55,320 --> 00:40:56,720
Well, well.

547
00:40:58,320 --> 00:41:00,480
So, you'll be at my side on the day?

548
00:41:01,680 --> 00:41:04,216
I thank you for the honour,
but I request permission

549
00:41:04,240 --> 00:41:06,776
to be allowed to fight on the
front line with my regiment.

550
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:08,456
It'll be bloody.

551
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:10,280
But you don't need me to tell you that.

552
00:41:11,720 --> 00:41:14,976
I expect to lose 200,000 men.

553
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:17,616
God-willing, he'll lose more.

554
00:41:17,640 --> 00:41:19,736
He thinks he's invincible.

555
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:21,360
He'll find he's not.

556
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:25,080
We're fighting on our own soil now.

557
00:41:26,080 --> 00:41:29,960
We can't give him a clear run
to Moscow, not without a fight.

558
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:32,000
So...

559
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:35,240
it has to be here.

560
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:40,480
We'll stop him here.
At Borodino.

561
00:41:41,680 --> 00:41:43,040
Good.

562
00:41:44,840 --> 00:41:46,040
Good luck, my boy.

563
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:49,080
I hope we meet again.

564
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:05,280
[SOLDIERS CHATTER]

565
00:42:13,120 --> 00:42:15,856
Excuse me, sir - what's this place called?

566
00:42:15,880 --> 00:42:17,936
Bordino... No, Borodino.

567
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:19,576
And are all these ours?

568
00:42:19,600 --> 00:42:22,056
That's right - and over there, the French.

569
00:42:22,080 --> 00:42:24,976
Look! There. You can see
their fires on the hill.

570
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:27,600
And you are, sir? What, a doctor?

571
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:29,936
No, no...

572
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:33,216
Um... I'm just here to see what's going on.

573
00:42:33,240 --> 00:42:36,000
[CHORAL VOICES NEARBY]

574
00:42:57,280 --> 00:43:00,000
[THEY SING REVERENTLY]

575
00:43:18,520 --> 00:43:19,920
[HE GRUNTS]

576
00:43:22,200 --> 00:43:23,480
Count Bezukhov!

577
00:43:24,880 --> 00:43:26,336
Dolokhov.

578
00:43:26,360 --> 00:43:28,760
[SINGING FADES INTO DISTANCE]

579
00:43:31,440 --> 00:43:33,840
I am so glad I saw you, old friend.

580
00:43:35,040 --> 00:43:38,480
God knows whether either of us
will be alive after tomorrow.

581
00:43:40,080 --> 00:43:42,080
I am very sorry we fell out.

582
00:43:43,120 --> 00:43:45,016
I wronged you, Petrushka,

583
00:43:45,040 --> 00:43:46,600
and I beg your forgiveness.

584
00:44:01,440 --> 00:44:07,320
[SHOUTS ECHO SUBDUED CONVERSATION]

585
00:44:11,520 --> 00:44:13,336
[HORSE NEIGHS]

586
00:44:13,360 --> 00:44:15,216
- Who is that fool?
[CLATTERING]

587
00:44:15,240 --> 00:44:17,536
- Hey, watch yourself!
- I do beg your pardon.

588
00:44:17,560 --> 00:44:19,656
I'm looking for Prince Bolkonsky.

589
00:44:19,680 --> 00:44:21,080
He's that way.

590
00:44:25,560 --> 00:44:27,200
Pierre?

591
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:31,416
- What in hell's name are you doing here?
- Looking for you!

592
00:44:31,440 --> 00:44:33,976
And I thought I would see if
there was anything I could do,

593
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:36,016
for Russia and so on...

594
00:44:36,040 --> 00:44:37,656
For God's sake, Pierre -

595
00:44:37,680 --> 00:44:40,016
we're about to fight the
bloodiest battle yet -

596
00:44:40,040 --> 00:44:41,640
I have to look after you now?

597
00:44:43,280 --> 00:44:46,856
You just turn around and go straight home,

598
00:44:46,880 --> 00:44:50,016
- while you still have the chance...
- No, no! I'm here now.

599
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:53,240
It's all right - I promise
I won't get in your way.

600
00:44:56,920 --> 00:44:58,240
Very well.

601
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:01,520
Come on, then.

602
00:45:09,960 --> 00:45:11,520
So, you think we'll win tomorrow?

603
00:45:12,960 --> 00:45:15,096
I think we'll hold them to a standstill,

604
00:45:15,120 --> 00:45:16,696
which is as good as winning.

605
00:45:16,720 --> 00:45:18,376
I sense it in our men.

606
00:45:18,400 --> 00:45:21,400
They're ready to die this
time, they won't run away.

607
00:45:23,920 --> 00:45:25,160
It won't be pretty.

608
00:45:26,760 --> 00:45:29,176
Really, you should go back to Moscow.

609
00:45:29,200 --> 00:45:32,776
No, no, not now I've come all this way.

610
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:34,856
I wouldn't miss it for the world.

611
00:45:34,880 --> 00:45:36,600
- You're not afraid?
- No!

612
00:45:38,520 --> 00:45:41,400
No, why should I be? If
death comes, it comes.

613
00:45:43,040 --> 00:45:45,256
What do I have to lose?

614
00:45:45,280 --> 00:45:47,680
I feel very much the same, my friend.

615
00:45:50,160 --> 00:45:52,216
I spoke to Natasha just before I came here.

616
00:45:52,240 --> 00:45:55,016
She still loves you, Andrei, and
she longs for your forgiveness.

617
00:45:55,040 --> 00:45:56,456
That's all over now,

618
00:45:56,480 --> 00:45:58,720
and I thought we'd agreed
we'd never speak of it.

619
00:46:14,200 --> 00:46:16,456
I went back to Bald Hills.

620
00:46:16,480 --> 00:46:19,136
I was walking through the orchard.

621
00:46:19,160 --> 00:46:22,936
There were a couple of peasant
girls there, very young,

622
00:46:22,960 --> 00:46:25,816
picking the plums and eating them.

623
00:46:25,840 --> 00:46:28,736
They thought they were
doing something naughty.

624
00:46:28,760 --> 00:46:31,560
When they saw me, they ran away laughing.

625
00:46:32,960 --> 00:46:35,680
I wanted to tell them, "It's all
right - take as many as you like."

626
00:46:38,320 --> 00:46:41,216
They were picking up their
skirts as they ran away.

627
00:46:41,240 --> 00:46:43,600
I could see their little feet...

628
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:46,120
flashing white.

629
00:46:53,920 --> 00:46:55,720
It was her soul I loved.

630
00:46:57,200 --> 00:46:58,640
Was it all an illusion?

631
00:47:05,360 --> 00:47:06,856
You know, one time,

632
00:47:06,880 --> 00:47:11,696
she was trying to tell me about
some old man she met in the forest,

633
00:47:11,720 --> 00:47:13,640
who'd been very kind to her.

634
00:47:14,720 --> 00:47:17,736
She was trying to find the
right words to tell it -

635
00:47:17,760 --> 00:47:19,520
how special the moment had been.

636
00:47:22,160 --> 00:47:25,160
She couldn't find the words,
but it didn't matter.

637
00:47:27,080 --> 00:47:28,776
It was in her eyes, Pierre.

638
00:47:28,800 --> 00:47:30,896
I know.

639
00:47:30,920 --> 00:47:32,936
- It was her soul I loved...
- I know.

640
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:34,480
And that animal, Kuragin...

641
00:47:35,680 --> 00:47:38,400
all he saw in her was a piece
of sweet flesh to feed on.

642
00:47:39,480 --> 00:47:41,416
Well, it's all over and done with, now.

643
00:47:41,440 --> 00:47:44,616
- No, it doesn't have to be.
- Enough. Time to sleep.

644
00:47:44,640 --> 00:47:46,696
You need to be fresh in
the morning and so do I.

645
00:47:46,720 --> 00:47:48,240
- Andrei...
- Enough!

646
00:48:01,600 --> 00:48:02,960
Warriors!

647
00:48:04,240 --> 00:48:07,656
Here, at last, is the
battle you longed for!

648
00:48:07,680 --> 00:48:12,040
Act as you acted at Austerlitz
and victory is assured!

649
00:48:13,880 --> 00:48:16,016
"Posterity will remember you"

650
00:48:16,040 --> 00:48:18,856
"as the heroes who fought and won"

651
00:48:18,880 --> 00:48:21,496
"in the great battle of Borodino!"

652
00:48:21,520 --> 00:48:24,336
[SOLDIERS]: - Vive I'Empereur!

653
00:48:24,360 --> 00:48:25,776
[RUMBLING EXPLOSION] What?

654
00:48:25,800 --> 00:48:27,376
[HORSES NEIGH]

655
00:48:27,400 --> 00:48:30,056
- What's happened? Has it begun?
- Yes, if you please.

656
00:48:30,080 --> 00:48:32,896
My master left a horse for you.
All the gentlemen have gone,

657
00:48:32,920 --> 00:48:34,896
and General Kutuzov left an hour ago.

658
00:48:34,920 --> 00:48:36,296
Why didn't you wake me?

659
00:48:36,320 --> 00:48:39,096
My master said to let you
sleep, Your Excellency.

660
00:48:39,120 --> 00:48:40,840
[SHOUTING OUTSIDE]

661
00:48:43,600 --> 00:48:46,200
Excuse me... I beg your pardon.

662
00:48:50,800 --> 00:48:53,480
Excuse me, excuse me...
I beg your pardon.

663
00:48:57,040 --> 00:49:03,000
[CANNONS FIRE IN DISTANCE]
[GUNFIRE]

664
00:49:19,000 --> 00:49:20,256
Who's that?

665
00:49:20,280 --> 00:49:21,680
You, sir!

666
00:49:22,960 --> 00:49:25,336
Count Bezukhov, at your
service, Your Grace.

667
00:49:25,360 --> 00:49:28,736
Anything I can do to help - I should
like to get in the thick of it!

668
00:49:28,760 --> 00:49:30,840
Oh! Would you now?

669
00:49:32,240 --> 00:49:34,880
All right, show him the way.

670
00:49:37,120 --> 00:49:39,136
God be with you, my boy.

671
00:49:39,160 --> 00:49:40,400
Follow me.

672
00:49:46,120 --> 00:49:50,720
[LOUD EXPLOSIONS AND SHOUTING]

673
00:49:52,520 --> 00:49:57,680
[CANNONS BOOM AND SHOUTING]

674
00:50:02,720 --> 00:50:06,056
Sir, you shouldn't be here.
It's too dangerous!

675
00:50:06,080 --> 00:50:08,176
It's all right. I won't get in the way.

676
00:50:08,200 --> 00:50:10,696
Let me know if there's anything I can do.

677
00:50:10,720 --> 00:50:13,896
[EXPLOSION, SCREAMING]
[PATTERING DEBRIS]

678
00:50:13,920 --> 00:50:16,496
Are you not scared, Master?

679
00:50:16,520 --> 00:50:17,896
No, I don't seem to be - are you?

680
00:50:17,920 --> 00:50:20,136
When you could have your
guts spilled at any minute?

681
00:50:20,160 --> 00:50:21,616
Of course I'm scared!

682
00:50:21,640 --> 00:50:26,520
[RUMBLING EXPLOSIONS]
[SCREAMING]

683
00:50:28,360 --> 00:50:30,800
[ALL MARCH IN SILENCE]

684
00:50:32,480 --> 00:50:34,360
[BOOMING EXPLOSION]

685
00:50:36,120 --> 00:50:42,320
[SCREAMING, THEY SHOUT]
[GROANING]

686
00:50:44,760 --> 00:50:46,680
[THEY SCREAM]

687
00:50:48,120 --> 00:50:49,616
[EXPLOSION]

688
00:50:49,640 --> 00:50:52,416
- We're getting cut to pieces!
- Nothing to do but endure.

689
00:50:52,440 --> 00:50:55,336
[STEADY MARCHING]

690
00:50:55,360 --> 00:50:57,456
- Courage, lads!
[THEY SHOUT]

691
00:50:57,480 --> 00:51:03,120
[CANNONS FIRE, EXPLOSIONS, SHOUTING]

692
00:51:06,320 --> 00:51:10,336
[HE YELLS]
[PATTERING DEBRIS]

693
00:51:10,360 --> 00:51:15,016
Colonel, it is my duty to report.
Only eight charges left.

694
00:51:15,040 --> 00:51:16,496
Do we continue firing?

695
00:51:16,520 --> 00:51:18,176
Yes, of course.

696
00:51:18,200 --> 00:51:20,696
You - run to the ammunition
cart, get the reserves!

697
00:51:20,720 --> 00:51:22,096
I'll go! I'm strong.

698
00:51:22,120 --> 00:51:24,920
- This is no place for you, Master.
- No, no, I'll help you carry them.

699
00:51:27,800 --> 00:51:32,656
[CRASHING EXPLOSIONS]
[SHOUTING AND GUNFIRE]

700
00:51:32,680 --> 00:51:35,760
[SCREAMING]

701
00:51:39,120 --> 00:51:42,840
[EXPLOSIONS]
Here they are, Master!

702
00:51:47,360 --> 00:51:54,920
[CRASHING BOOM]
[WIND WHISTLES]

703
00:51:57,000 --> 00:52:00,920
[SILENCE]
[TINNITUS WHINE]

704
00:52:33,600 --> 00:52:35,960
[DISTANT SHOUTING]

705
00:52:47,800 --> 00:52:51,176
WHIZZING PROJECTILE EXPLOSION

706
00:52:51,200 --> 00:52:53,576
[SHOUTING]
[GUNFIRE]

707
00:52:53,600 --> 00:52:56,416
Sir, the ammunition boxes got blown up!

708
00:52:56,440 --> 00:52:58,160
[SCREAMING]

709
00:53:02,360 --> 00:53:04,616
Help me, brother! Help me!

710
00:53:04,640 --> 00:53:08,750
[FRENCH SOLDIER ROARS]
[THEY GRUNT]

711
00:53:08,775 --> 00:53:10,144
[GRUNTING]

712
00:53:14,440 --> 00:53:21,000
[PATTERING DEBRIS]
[SCREAMING SOLDIERS SHOUT]

713
00:53:23,080 --> 00:53:25,080
[THEY SHOUT]

714
00:53:37,160 --> 00:53:39,456
Sire, Marshal Murat's compliments.

715
00:53:39,480 --> 00:53:41,536
Reinforcements are necessary!

716
00:53:41,560 --> 00:53:43,896
Reinforcements? We're only two to one!

717
00:53:43,920 --> 00:53:47,416
Marshal Murat says one more
division would finish the job.

718
00:53:47,440 --> 00:53:51,256
Sire, the Russians are attacking our
left flank! We can't hold them!

719
00:53:51,280 --> 00:53:53,656
- Sire - the Imperial Guard?
- No.

720
00:53:53,680 --> 00:53:56,696
I'm not going to risk losing the
Imperial Guard in this shambles.

721
00:53:56,720 --> 00:53:58,856
Order the army to withdraw and regroup.

722
00:53:58,880 --> 00:54:01,496
Meanwhile, keep up with the bombardment.

723
00:54:01,520 --> 00:54:03,880
THERE'S MORE THAN ONE WAY TO SKIN A CAT.

724
00:54:05,520 --> 00:54:07,560
[GUNFIRE STOPS]

725
00:54:11,560 --> 00:54:15,616
[DOG PANTS, DOG WHINES and THEY LAUGH]

726
00:54:15,640 --> 00:54:16,880
Look at that dog!

727
00:54:18,200 --> 00:54:20,176
The things you see in a war.

728
00:54:20,200 --> 00:54:21,896
[PROJECTILE WHIZZES]
Look out!

729
00:54:21,920 --> 00:54:25,080
[PATTERING DEBRIS]
Get down, sir!

730
00:54:25,840 --> 00:54:27,056
Get down, sir!

731
00:54:27,080 --> 00:54:28,216
Get down!

732
00:54:28,240 --> 00:54:31,800
[FUSE HISSES]

733
00:54:37,400 --> 00:54:41,480
[HISSING SILENCE]

734
00:54:43,880 --> 00:54:51,767
[EXPLOSION, SOLDIERS GROAN AND SOB WAILING]

735
00:54:53,045 --> 00:54:55,181
SOLDIER CONVULSES

736
00:54:55,205 --> 00:54:59,084
SOLDIER SCREAMS,
SAW RASPS SOBBING

737
00:55:00,408 --> 00:55:04,896
MUFFLED SCREAMS All
right, Your Excellency.

738
00:55:04,920 --> 00:55:07,386
It's a bad one, but we'll do our best.

739
00:55:07,410 --> 00:55:13,736
[SAW RASPS]
[SOLDIER WHIMPERS SOBBING]

740
00:55:13,760 --> 00:55:19,856
[COUGHING, HE MOANS]
[CRUNCHING, SNAP, HE GASPS]

741
00:55:19,880 --> 00:55:21,696
Show it to me...!

742
00:55:21,720 --> 00:55:23,336
There you are, sir.

743
00:55:23,360 --> 00:55:25,160
[HE HYPERVENTILATES]

744
00:55:26,920 --> 00:55:28,256
Anatole?

745
00:55:28,280 --> 00:55:29,816
Anatole.

746
00:55:29,840 --> 00:55:31,216
Kuragin.

747
00:55:31,240 --> 00:55:33,056
Bolkonsky.

748
00:55:33,080 --> 00:55:35,840
Bolkonsky, have pity.

749
00:55:36,840 --> 00:55:38,336
Look what they've done to me!

750
00:55:38,360 --> 00:55:40,440
[HE GROANS]

751
00:55:51,800 --> 00:55:55,960
[ANATOLE SOBS, HE TAKES DEEP BREATHS]

752
00:56:54,960 --> 00:56:57,176
Gentlemen, we have endured everything

753
00:56:57,200 --> 00:56:59,920
the enemy could throw at us
and have driven them off.

754
00:57:01,200 --> 00:57:05,576
Napoleon has suffered a mortal wound
from which he will not recover.

755
00:57:05,600 --> 00:57:09,176
The spirit of his army has been broken.

756
00:57:09,200 --> 00:57:10,520
And now?

757
00:57:11,800 --> 00:57:13,120
Do we go on the offensive?

758
00:57:15,560 --> 00:57:17,656
No.

759
00:57:17,680 --> 00:57:19,080
We retreat.

760
00:57:20,120 --> 00:57:22,816
We lost half our army at Borodino.

761
00:57:22,840 --> 00:57:25,096
Let us not lose the other half.

762
00:57:25,120 --> 00:57:26,760
Abandon Moscow?

763
00:57:27,920 --> 00:57:30,720
Abandon Russia's sacred
capital without a fight?

